The article discusses the importance of creating opportunities for American workers to secure long-term, fulfilling careers. It highlights the establishment of the National Council for the American Worker and the American Workforce Policy Advisory Board to address workforce development issues through collaboration between the education and business sectors. The President has also called on businesses to invest in their workforce by expanding programs that educate and reskill American workers. The goal is to lift marginalized workers back into the workforce and provide them with family-sustaining careers.